10. SUCI CONCEALMENT in 5G simulator
    Currently: gNB sends plaintext SUPI (IMSI) as "suci" field
    Change to: proper SUCI encoding per TS 33.501 §6.12.2
    - Use OpenSSL ECDH (curve: secp256r1 / P-256)
    - UDM holds the Home Network Public Key
    - gNB encrypts IMSI into SUCI using ECIES (HKDF-SHA256 + AES-128-CTR + HMAC-SHA256)
    - AMF receives SUCI (encrypted), forwards to UDM
    - UDM decrypts SUCI → SUPI, then proceeds with auth
    - AMF never sees the raw IMSI — only SUPI after UDM confirms
    - Add INTERVIEW log: explain why SUCI exists (prevents IMSI catchers)
    Reference: TS 33.501 §6.12, TS 23.003 §2.2B

11. PFCP between SMF and UPF in 5G simulator
    Add UPF (User Plane Function) node:
    - SMF establishes PFCP session with UPF (TS 29.244)
    - SMF sends PFCP Session Establishment Request with PDRs and FARs
    - UPF responds with PFCP Session Establishment Response
    - Write PFCP packets to pcap (UDP port 8805)
    - Add INTERVIEW narration explaining control/user plane separation (CUPS)

